# Tailwind CSS Configuration and Usage

## Configuration Files
- [src/index.css](mdc:src/index.css) - Contains Tailwind directives
- [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js) - Tailwind configuration

## Tailwind Directives
The following directives are required in [src/index.css](mdc:src/index.css):
```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;
```

## Content Configuration
Tailwind is configured to scan the following files for utility classes:
```js
content: [
  "./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}",
  "./components/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}",
  "./app/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx,mdx}",
]
```

## Best Practices

### Utility-First Approach
- Use Tailwind utility classes directly in components
- Avoid custom CSS unless necessary
- Use component composition for reusable styles

### Responsive Design
- Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
- Mobile-first approach
- Maintain consistent breakpoints

### Dark Mode
- Use dark: prefix for dark mode styles
- Maintain color consistency
- Test both light and dark modes

### Performance
- PurgeCSS enabled by default
- Only used utilities are included in production
- Keep bundle size optimized

### Component Examples
```jsx
// Button Example
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-500 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-600">
  Click Me
</button>

// Card Example
<div className="p-6 max-w-sm mx-auto bg-white rounded-xl shadow-md">
  <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Card Title</h2>
  <p className="text-gray-600">Card content goes here</p>
</div>
```

### Custom Extensions
- Extend theme in tailwind.config.js
- Define custom colors
- Create custom plugins when needed
- Use @apply for complex, reusable patterns
